wanIfIndex.name: wanIfIndex
wanIfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. 1 - Private port 2 - Public port

wanIfFramesRcvd.name: wanIfFramesRcvd
wanIfFramesRcvd.description: Total frames received on this interface.

wanIfFramesXmit.name: wanIfFramesXmit
wanIfFramesXmit.description: Total frames transmitted on this interface.

wanIfFramesDisc.name: wanIfFramesDisc
wanIfFramesDisc.description: Total frames discarded on this interface.

wanIfRcvOvrn.name: wanIfRcvOvrn
wanIfRcvOvrn.description: Total frames received on this interface with data overrun errors.

wanIfRcvAbort.name: wanIfRcvAbort
wanIfRcvAbort.description: Total frames received on this interface aborted by the sender.

wanIfRcvAlignErr.name: wanIfRcvAlignErr
wanIfRcvAlignErr.description: Total frames received on this interface with alignment errors.

wanIfRcvCRCErr.name: wanIfRcvCRCErr
wanIfRcvCRCErr.description: Total frames received on this interface with CRC errors.

wanIfRcvFrameLong.name: wanIfRcvFrameLong
wanIfRcvFrameLong.description: Total frames received on this interface with length errors.

wanIfRcvNoBuff.name: wanIfRcvNoBuff
wanIfRcvNoBuff.description: Total frames for which there were no receive buffers available.

wanIfXmitUnderrun.name: wanIfXmitUnderrun
wanIfXmitUnderrun.description: Total frames with transmit underrun errors.

wanIfXmitTimeout.name: wanIfXmitTimeout
wanIfXmitTimeout.description: Total times we've timed out trying to transmit a frame.

wanIfXmitNoBuff.name: wanIfXmitNoBuff
wanIfXmitNoBuff.description: Total times there were no transmit buffers available when trying to transmit a frame.

wanIfRcvByteRate.name: wanIfRcvByteRate
wanIfRcvByteRate.description: last 16 second average KB per second of data received.

wanIfXmitByteRate.name: wanIfXmitByteRate
wanIfXmitByteRate.description: last 16 second average KB per second of data sent.

vpnIndex.name: vpnIndex
vpnIndex.description: A unique value for each VPN. Ranges from 1 to (number of VPNs configured + number of clients configured). So, this table will not map 1-to-1 with the VPNs configured via VPNmanager when VPNRemote clients are configured as part of a VPN. Each client has it's own physical VPN on a VSU.

vpnDescr.name: vpnDescr
vpnDescr.description: Textual description of this interface. Currently (1/9/98) just shows the VPN decimal id.

vpnSkipInPktDecap.name: vpnSkipInPktDecap
vpnSkipInPktDecap.description: Total incoming SKIP-decapsulated packets for this VPN.

vpnSkipOutPktEncap.name: vpnSkipOutPktEncap
vpnSkipOutPktEncap.description: Total outgoing SKIP-encapsulated packets for this VPN.

vpnSkipInPktParseErr.name: vpnSkipInPktParseErr
vpnSkipInPktParseErr.description: Total incoming packets for this VPN with IPSec header errors.

vpnSkipInKPUpdt.name: vpnSkipInKPUpdt
vpnSkipInKPUpdt.description: Number of Kp (key material) updates for incoming traffic this VPN. Not currently supported.

vpnSkipOutKPUpdt.name: vpnSkipOutKPUpdt
vpnSkipOutKPUpdt.description: Number of Kp (key material) updates for outgoing traffic this VPN. Not currently supported.

vpnOutFrag.name: vpnOutFrag
vpnOutFrag.description: Total outgoing packets for this VPN that had to be fragmented.

vpnOctetsIn.name: vpnOctetsIn
vpnOctetsIn.description: Total bytes received for this VPN.

vpnOctetsOut.name: vpnOctetsOut
vpnOctetsOut.description: Total bytes sent for this VPN.

vpnNOutOfOrder.name: vpnNOutOfOrder
vpnNOutOfOrder.description: Counter N out-of-order errors for this VPN. Not currently supported.

vpnSkipAlgMismatch.name: vpnSkipAlgMismatch
vpnSkipAlgMismatch.description: Total number of packets belonging to this VPN with SKIP Algorithm mismatches. That is, the parameters of the VPN that this packet belongs to does not match the VPN parameters in the packet's SKIP header.

vpnAuthInPktInvdSig.name: vpnAuthInPktInvdSig
vpnAuthInPktInvdSig.description: Total number of packets belonging to this VPN with SKIP Authentication errors. That is, the authentication key in the offending packet was not correct. This type of attack results in an authFailure trap which shows up on the VPNmanager as Invalid Authentication Signature.

vpnEncryptImpEncap.name: vpnEncryptImpEncap
vpnEncryptImpEncap.description: Total outgoing packets encrypted for this VPN.

vpnEncryptInPktParseErr.name: vpnEncryptInPktParseErr
vpnEncryptInPktParseErr.description: Total packets belonging to this VPN that had parse errors. For example, encrypted data was not on a 8-byte boundary or the ESP trailer was not of the appropriate size.

logAttackType.name: logAttackType
logAttackType.description: The type of packet error that caused us to perceive this as an attack. 1 - SKIP header error. e.g. this packet was not IPSec AH or IPSec ESP. 2 - SKIP Counter N error. Not currently (1/9/98) supported. 3 - SKIP Algorithm mismatch. The parameters of the VPN that this packet belongs to does not match the VPN parameters in the SKIP header. 4 - SKIP Authentication error. The authentication key in the offending packet was not correct. This type of attack results in an authFailure trap which shows up on the VPNmanager as Invalid Authentication Signature. 5 - SKIP Authentication Header error. Not supported. 6 - SKIP Encryption Header error. The packet's ESP trailer wasn't correct.

asName.name: asName
asName.description: A VPNremote client name or a VSU name as defined in VPNmanager.

asLength.name: asLength
asLength.description: Length of this session in seconds.

asOrgIPAddress.name: asOrgIPAddress
asOrgIPAddress.description: VPNremote client's originating IP address or remote VSU IP address.

asXlateIPAddress.name: asXlateIPAddress
asXlateIPAddress.description: VPNremote client's assigned address from the Client IP Address pool if configured. If the Client IP Address pool is not configured or this session is from a VSU then this attribute is empty.

asDescr.name: asDescr
asDescr.description: Textual description of this VPN indicating what key management is being used and what encryption, authentication and compression algorithms are being used. For example: IKE, 3DES, MD5, Compression.

asPktsIn.name: asPktsIn
asPktsIn.description: Number of packets sent to this VSU from the VPNremote Client or remote VSU indicated by asName during this session.

asPktsOut.name: asPktsOut
asPktsOut.description: Number of packets sent from this VSU to the VPNremote Client or remote VSU indicated by asName during this session.

asBytesIn.name: asBytesIn
asBytesIn.description: Number of bytes sent to this VSU from the VPNremote Client or remote VSU indicated by asName during this session.

asBytesOut.name: asBytesOut
asBytesOut.description: Number of bytes sent from this VSU to the VPNremote Client or remote VSU indicated by asName during this session.

skipHdrErr.name: skipHdrErr
skipHdrErr.description: SKIP header error. e.g. this packet was not IPSec AH or IPSec ESP.

skipNCounterErr.name: skipNCounterErr
skipNCounterErr.description: SKIP Count N error. Not used.

skipAlgMismatch.name: skipAlgMismatch
skipAlgMismatch.description: SKIP Algorithm mismatch. The parameters of the VPN that a packet belonged to did not match the VPN parameters in the SKIP header.

authFailure.name: authFailure
authFailure.description: SKIP Authentication error. The authentication key in the offending packet was not correct. This trap shows up on the VPNmanager as Invalid Authentication Signature.

authHdrErr.name: authHdrErr
authHdrErr.description: SKIP Authentication Header error. Not used.

encryptHdrErr.name: encryptHdrErr
encryptHdrErr.description: SKIP Encryption Header error. The packet's ESP trailer wasn't correct.

authFailureLimitErr.name: authFailureLimitErr
authFailureLimitErr.description: Client Configuration Download failure limit reached.
